<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id12255558-e3ef-11ef-8e9f-f6e47fd25777" identifier="/us/usc/t44/s1304"><num value="1304">§ 1304.</num><heading> Army and Navy registers</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">In addition to the usual number of the registers of the Army and Navy, fifteen hundred copies of each shall be printed: five hundred for the Senate, and one thousand for the House of Representatives.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id12279f49-e3ef-11ef-8e9f-f6e47fd25777">(<ref href="/us/pl/90/620">Pub. L. 90–620</ref>, <date date="1968-10-22">Oct. 22, 1968</date>, § <ref href="/us/stat/82/1266">82 Stat. 1266</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
